Zestrenocya Zephryfyst, the happiest taxi driver in Norrath <BR>
Guild Administrator (That's a really nice term for "secretary") of Silent Redemption <BR>
Proprietor: Norrath's Finest Taxi Service <BR>
<A HREF="http://sr.amiga.tm/" TARGET="_new"><IMG ALT="Silent Redemption Member" BORDER=0 SRC="http://fairblade.sinbad.net/images/SRlogo.gif"></A>


</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujuujuu.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Juujuu</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 781<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/13/01 8:37:31 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://daydream-graphics.com/artists/hoover/qhorcishhealer.jpg width=112 height=90></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ***DISCUSSION -- FIRE GIANT VOTE***</span><hr size=1> There are other semi long spawn time mobs that are not reserved.  Examples of this are Hadden, and that guard in HH that is used for the Testament of Vanaer quest.  Anyone who thinks that these should be reserved would be laughed at, yet Fire Giants have the same kind of spawn time, but people think they should be reserved.  I want consistancy, which is part of why I vote no.<br>
<br>
Supposedly FGs are used as a training ground to learn how to lead a raid.  If this is the reason they are being reserved, they shouldn't be.  There are many many better places to lead a raid.  Examples of this are Lower Guk King raid, fighting from one zone to the other in Kael Drakkel, fight your way through the entire castle in Castle Mistmoore, fight just past the drop off in the Hole, do a run through Runnyeye, fight from zone in to zone out in Sebilis, etc.  If you are practicing leading a raid, you don't need really high level mobs to learn how to coordinate groups.  You need communication.  Reserving FGs is unnecessary when there are so many other places you can practice raiding.  This is part of why I vote no.<br>
<br>
Currently, the few times I reserve Fire Giants, it's purely 100% a farming effort.  The goal is to get some xp, a PMM for the druid/cleric with me, a PMT for the ranger/SK/paladin or Tranix Crown for random to all/or to cawu, and to get some mithral armor to sell for a quick 2k.  About 90% of all raids I see on FGs are farming efforts and/or hoping to get Ragefire up.  There shouldn't be anything in the game capable of being farmed by 2 people and reservable. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unadiabrell.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nadia brell</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 158<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/13/01 9:23:57 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://home.earthlink.net/~karl23/_images/nadia.jpg width=99 height=150></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ***DISCUSSION -- FIRE GIANT VOTE***</span><hr size=1> &lt;About 90% of all raids I see on FGs are farming efforts and/or hoping to get Ragefire up.&gt;<br>
<br>
You think you can farm with a crew of 30 lowbie 40s ?):P <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukeyanaubaine.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Keyan Aubaine</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 125<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/13/01 10:44:05 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ***DISCUSSION -- FIRE GIANT VOTE***</span><hr size=1> It's what ? the 3rd, maybe 4th time we vote on this ?<br>
<br>
If i was voting i'd vote yes just so people stop talking about the fucking place.<br>
It'll end up FFA like the rest of the server at some point anyway, giving small guilds a few more months wont change squat to the final result.<br>
<br>
Besides, what exactly happened to the idea a few people supported to only make them reservable 2 days a week ?<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uganonstormwynd.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ganon Stormwynd</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.angelfire.com/il/selectevil/icons/Icon_Fire.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 226<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/14/01 2:27:11 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http:\\www.righteousfire.com/images/gano1.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ***DISCUSSION -- FIRE GIANT VOTE***</span><hr size=1> Get rid of the ability to reserve them.  It's causing too many problems with Ragefire, and it's not an exclusive raiding area as it was a year ago.<br>
<br>
There are numerous other spots to practice raiding:<br>
<br>
Kael<br>
Velketor's<br>
Skyshrine<br>
Icewell Keep<br>
Sebilis<br>
Howling Stones<br>
Western Wastes<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unadiabrell.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nadia brell</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 160<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/14/01 4:39:24 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://home.earthlink.net/~karl23/_images/nadia.jpg width=99 height=150></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ***DISCUSSION -- FIRE GIANT VOTE***</span><hr size=1> I agree with your points Ganon<br>
<br>
I think there are OTHER places that EVERYONE can hunt in<br>
<br>
special treatment shouldnt be given for epics, imo<br>
<br>
-- I dont see why Epic questers cannot cooperate with FG raiders who made reservations<br>
(half the time FGs are First Come First Serve anyhow)<br>
<br>
<br>
The pros of raiding at that particular spot<br>
(this assumes you have a crew of 24+ lowbie 40 raiders)<br>
======================================================<br>
1.  Raid can organize at a druid circle  <br>
<br>
no easier spot in the game for **transporting** people to a raid -- very helpful for lowbie/newbie raiders<br>
<br>
...  Try getting 24 people **on time** to a spot -- many who havent raided before<br>
<br>
..   When Ive run my raids, I get no shows and latecomers and always end up with 30 people going in (I DONT NEED 30 people -- but if 30 people want to go, so be it)<br>
<br>
2.  Low spam in Lavastorm for making announcements pre-raid<br>
<br>
3.  Raid has a linear approach to what needs to be done in 2 or 3 hours -- and there's a LITERAL END to the raid when you finish clearing them.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
just because a group of 4 55+ people can *also* kill FGs with greater ease than a crew of lowbie raiders means NOTHING but a putdown in my eyes.<br>
<br>
why do those kind of comments need to be said ?<br>
<br>
who cares if 4 people can kill what 30 people can also kill?<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unadiabrell.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nadia brell</A> at: 4/14/01 4:44:03 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubranndamere.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Branndamere</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/14/01 4:42:26 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ***DISCUSSION -- FIRE GIANT VOTE***</span><hr size=1> My only hangup with FGs being unreservable is a Naggy raid potentially NOT knowing when they were taken down. Yes, there are lots of other raidable places, I totally agree with that. But will not knowing the time of clearing on FGs cause problems for Naggy raids? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udauros.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dauros</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 104<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/14/01 5:42:40 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ***DISCUSSION -- FIRE GIANT VOTE***</span><hr size=1> Leave them alone.<br>
<br>
People can coordinate and plan around for ragefire just like they do for nagafen. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utoril.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Toril</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/14/01 10:35:36 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ***DISCUSSION -- FIRE GIANT VOTE***</span><hr size=1> Thank you Nadia. :-)<br>
<br>
Ganon DID suggested plenty of places for raid practice:<br>
<br>
                         Kael<br>
                         Velketor's<br>
                         Skyshrine<br>
                         Icewell Keep<br>
                         Sebilis<br>
                         Howling Stones<br>
                         Western Wastes<br>
<br>
However, how are you supposed to give the 40-45's raid practice in 50+ zones? :-) That's why Danforth and I started the UNB FG raids; a lot of our people were getting close to 46 and we wanted to send them out with SOME experience. My first Hate went painlessly (also thanks to Evoluxa :-)) because I sort of knew what to expect.<br>
<br>
Practicing in a zone where all the mobs are green and there is very little danger does not give new raiders ANY experience with: the sense of imminent death, needing to be in melee range to cast, 3-pronged timed attacks such as on Vox (OK, FG's doesn't give that either), wipeouts, CR...I agree that ANY dungeon is useful for practicing communication, but hunting greenies does not...give enough of a sence of urgency to make people show up on time and pay attention.  And, sadly to say, quite a few people are NOT going to want go on a practice raid in a zone where there is no loot they can use.<br>
<br>
I do agree that a lot of FG raids ARE for loot, but imaking them non-reservable just because some people (anyone having reason to be in that area, whether they be a Naggy raid, FG raid or cleric) won't or don't know how to compromise is giving those of us who can only play during peak hours the shaft.<br>
<br>
Can't there be some sort of compromise on this?  Is there any way to make them reservable on alternate days, like 3 days off, then 3 days on?  The dates should be selected by the moderator, I guess, and posted<br>
no later than the 22d of the previous month.<br>
<br>
