 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaeremoggstormsummoner.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aeremogg Stormsummoner</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 278<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/14/01 10:51:36 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ***DISCUSSION -- FIRE GIANT VOTE***</span><hr size=1> all i notice is the uber epic hungry people voting no =) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bbrellserilis.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=binge>Binge</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_bluespot.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>wang</span><br>  Posts: 1045<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/14/01 10:58:08 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.wyattweb.com/users/monkeyo/monkey.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ***DISCUSSION -- FIRE GIANT VOTE***</span><hr size=1> The only things reservable are Nag/Vox, Trak and VS.  4 things.  Theres what, 80 dragons in Norrath now?! (wee bit of exaggeration)<br>
<br>
FG are easy.  Fire giants are killable with 1 group or less now.  And yes, Ragefire might be part of my concern (being a cleric, who's gonna need ragefire very soon), but even before I started working on my Epic i thought reserving them was silly.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umajentasdiamondheart.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Majentas Diamondheart</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 33<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/14/01 11:44:03 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ***DISCUSSION -- FIRE GIANT VOTE***</span><hr size=1> Ok,  my quick take on this, <br>
You have all listed great places to try learning to lead a raid, but, look at it closely, every one of those places are not reservable, so it is very hard to set up a time and date that you can get a whole bunch of people to this spot, and guarentee you are not walking on anybody elses toes, in other words, what one of those zones can you go into, lead a perfectly smooth raid (being it is a raid leading learning experience) and not have to deal with all the other campers.... I want to learn to lead a raid, so I will take people somewhere that no other groups should be at that time. How many times does a raid party port to Hate and see it camped already? /bonk<br>
Anyhow, just a Raiding noobie veiw <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Thank you for your time.... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/urykilth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rykilth</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_bluespot.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 297<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/14/01 12:50:39 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://cpl.net/~kurtds/pic/rykilth.jpg height=125 width=125></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ***DISCUSSION -- FIRE GIANT VOTE***</span><hr size=1> Remove the reservation system for Firegiants, it's causing way to many problems with Ragefire. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujuujuu.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Juujuu</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 784<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/14/01 2:13:26 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://216.242.60.166/chicktourney_com/larges/415.jpg width=110 height=200></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ***DISCUSSION -- FIRE GIANT VOTE***</span><hr size=1> Kael<br>
Icewell Keep<br>
You can bind in both of these locations.  There's lots and lots of mobs to kill in these zones.  The spawn time is fast enough that there will keep being stuff to kill after you've killed it once.  There's very very few people actively hunting each of these zones.<br>
<br>
Velketor's<br>
Mobs here would give xp to my high 40s paladin.  It gives you an excellent chance to learn to coordinate lots of people, especially since the floors are slippery.  There's your sense of death.  If you don't listen, you fall down and die to a train of green/blue spiders.<br>
<br>
Skyshrine<br>
Varying difficulties of mobs for raids of all sizes and levels.  Mobs drop planar quality armor at the zone, and better stuff deep inside.  You can sow in the zone for easier CR.<br>
<br>
Sebilis<br>
Lots of people here already, so doing a raid will be tough unless you go for myconids.  Fight your way to the Juggs.  1 Jugg = 1 Fire Giant with higher than normal MR.  This is the ideal place to lead a raid.  Nice armor, weapon, and spell drops come from here.  If Trak is down, you can even take on Jumpalot and the Protector.<br>
<br>
Howling Stones<br>
Few people hunt in this zone.  Long distances to travel through each wing to get to the &quot;end&quot; wing (east is it?  or south)<br>
<br>
Western Wastes<br>
Excellent place to raid.  You can port into Cobolt Scar which is only 2 zones away from WW.  Getting through Siren's Ghetto is no longer the headache it used to be.  There's lots of easy dragons to kill which only take 12? to 18 people to kill.  They drop high level equipment and weapons and quest items.  CR isn't all that hard since invis works vs most of the mobs in zone.  Zone is big enough for multiple simotaneous raids<br>
<br>
Dragon Nec<br>
Excellent place to raid.  Only 1 zone farther away than WW.  Invis works for doing CR.  Easy to zone in and out to get sow.  Awesome weapon and some decent armor drops.  Quest gems drop here.  Some decent quest items drop too.  A single well organized group can hunt here, or do like we saw the other day and bring in 5 groups to work together.  I saw about 3 or 4 of the warriors in nearly full crafted, but their raid was going fine for the most part.  Zone is big enough for multiple simotaneous raids.<br>
<br>
