It's not about cooperation.  It's partially about people using the FG reservations as a means of reserving Ragefire, which is not a reservable spawn.  That goes against the rules themselves and the spirit of those rules.<br>
<br>
The original purpose, as I remember it, to reserving Fire Giants was to give the 40s crowd some place to raid and learn their raid tactics.  Fire Giants are no longer needed for this.  There are lots of other places to raid that serve this purpose.<br>
<br>
There are lots of places for mid 40s raiders to raid and learn their raid tactics.  <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Kaesora</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> is a Low 40s dungeon full of undead and spiders and it's like a maze so if you don't learn how to get around you can easily get lost.  This place also drops some awesome loot for the mid to low 40s crowd.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Mines of Nurga</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> is a neat dungeon to crawl.  It's the right level for the upper 30s to 40s crowd to check out and learn their tactics.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Temple of Droga</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> is next to Mines of Nurga and is a another nice dungeon to crawl.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> City of Mist</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> is a great place for loot and exp.  It's also a great place to learn how to adapt to bad pathing and warping mobs.  A 40 something crowd may not be able to go the whole distance of the zone, but they certainly could take on a reaver or two and learn some very interesting tactics.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Ice Giants</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> will challenge your skill more than Fire Giants because of their fast respawn time.  Plus this area has some very interesting traps and such to it.  It's a great way to also learn the area before going on a Vox raid.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Ganon mentioned several places, a few of them would work well others wouldn't work for the 40s crowd.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Kael</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> - Actually, this a great place for raiders to get to know raiding.  Deep in would be another story, but the front ends of zone would serve a useful purpose to learning raid tactics.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Velketor's</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> - won't even talk on it.  The only thing I know of this zone is that it's not a place for me.  With all the hanging walk ways and bridges and the slick ice... can you say... I don't think so!<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Skyshrine</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> - Great zone for a 40s crew to raid.  Also has some great drops.  40s crew wouldn't be able to go all the way, but could crawl it and learn raid tactics.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Icewell Keep</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> - I've never been here, but my guild family has and they were all love to mid 50s at the time.  I don't think this is a wise place for a low to mid 40s group to raid at.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Sebilis</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> - Sorry Ganon, but you must be joking!!  This place is Lower Guk II, no raiding to be had here, unless you are a 50s crew going after Shrooms, Juggs or Trak.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Howling Stones</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> - Ya know... The Clan has lived in this for many levels at a time.  It's a great place for exp camps.  It's great to crawl each of the wings.  However, it's not a place I would recommend to the low 40s crowd.  Maybe and upper 40s crowd with a few 50s friends to help out.  I definitely wouldn't try the South or East wing as a 40 something a sufficient number of people.  Only thing that detours this from being a raiding zone is the key is difficult to get and not everyone has it.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Western Wastes</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> - Not a place for the 40s crowd.  This place is full of a bunch of Nagafen and Vox's.  50+ zone, in my opinion.<br>
